---
title: Lean Singapore Rice with Cashews and Bok Choi
description: Riding high on the crest of your feedback from his Singapore Laksa, Patrick has decided to take another trip to the hawker centres of the Far East for tonight’s dinner. Like it’s slinky sibling Singapore Noodles, this dish has that wonderful clash of flavours from India and the Far East that we so love at the Fresh Farm. As ever, be careful you don’t burn your nuts in the pan and go easy with the fish sauce - we recommend adding it bit by bit until the seasoning is just right.
